tax institute and other professional organizations he served as a parttime faculty member at the university of southern california master of business taxation program and is a member of the board of advisors for the leventhal school of accounting at usc phil is also on the advisory board for the graduate tax program at loyola law school active in his community phil serves in leadership positions on many nonprofit boards he is a graduate of the university of southern california summa cum laude holding a master’s degree in taxation and bachelor’s degree in business administration he received his jd from loyola law school order of the coif phil is a recipient of the elijah watt sells award phil began his career at kpmg llp professional experiencekpmg llp professional and community involvementamerican institute of certified public accountantscalifornia society of certified public accountantsamerican bar associationcalifornia state barlos angeles county bar associationworld presidents’ organization angeleno and los angeles chaptersharvardwestlake school board of trusteesuniversity of southern california leventhal school of accounting board of advisorsloyola law school graduate tax program advisory boardmusic center leadership councilascent capital group board member honors  awardsla the  most influential people in los angeles  the los angeles business journal hcvt in the news the smart way to pay taxes on retirement savings philip holthouse interviewed by chicago tribune practice area  specialization tax industries served real estate  hospitality private equity  investment advisory professional services firms high net worth individuals and family offices credentials and certificationscpa californiastate bar of californiaeducationmbt university of southern californiajd loyola law school order of the coifbs business administration university of southern california summa cum laude main menu contact us client login camarillo encino long beach los angeles orange county pasade