folio take a free trial to bloomberg bna tax  accounting bloomberg bna tax  accounting this portfolio is available with a subscription to bloomberg bna tax  accounting a comprehensive research solution including over  tax management portfolios practice tools primary sources and timely news free trial description authors table of contents working papers related products description tax management portfolio real estate leases no nd analyzes the tax issues encountered by both lessor and lessee in contemporary leases of real property this portfolio discusses issues to be considered in originating a lease including § rental agreements it also presents the lessors and lessees perspectives with respect to tax principles in determining who should pay for lessee improvements also discussed are the issues raised when a lease is modified terminated or transferred there are different reasons for using a sale of real property by its owner and the simultaneous leaseback of the property as a method of financing the property as opposed to borrowing this portfolio analyzes the income tax consequences to the sellerlessee and the buyerlessor and outlines the various tax problems inherent in structuring such transactions special emphasis is placed on tax planning from the standpoints of both the sellerlessee and the buyerlessor to maximize the tax benefits inherent in sale and leaseback and related transactions authors philip j holthouse philip j holthouse bs university of southern california summa cum laude  mbt university of southern california  jd loyola law school — los angeles order of the coif  adjunct professor university of southern california master of business taxation program – author of numerous articles on federal taxation member of the american bar association state bar of california american institute of certified public accountants california society of cpas partner holthouse carlin  van trigt llp cpas partner sherry meyerhoff hanson  crance llp attorneys at law lisa marie starczewski lisa marie starczewski jd summa cum laude villanova university school of law ba magna cum laude smith college starczewski served as editorinchief of the villanova law review – and has practiced law with morgan lewis  bockius and schnader harrison segal  lewis she taught at villanova university school of law ms starczewski has authored and coauthored several accounting policy and practice portfolios including  revenue recognition fundamental principles and  accounting for leases fundamental principles she has also authored numerous tax management portfolios including  tm installment sakes  tm partnerships — allocation of liabilities basis rules  tm noncorporate alternative minimum tax  tm corporate alternative minimum tax  tm irs national office procedures — rulings closing agreements  tm atrisk rules coauthor  tm scholarships and educational expenses she is also the author and coauthor of numerous tax practice series chapters she has received the tax management distinguished author award is a member of the tax management us income advisory board and is a consultant with buchanan ingersoll  rooney pc table of contents detailed analysis i introduction a what is a lease b types of leaseholds c rental terms ii originating a lease a negotiationseconomics  landlords perspective  tenants perspective  involving the tax advisor b accounting methods  landlords perspective a rental income  all events test applied  advance rentalsprepaid rent  advances as loans  security deposits distinguished b general expenses c real estate taxes d allocations among coâ€“owners  tenants perspective a accrual basis tenant b cash basis tenant c receipt of lease incentives  related party issues a section  b constructive receipt c passive loss interplay d excessive rent e section   tenant acquires equity or option c transaction costs  landlords perspective  tenants perspective  other landlord expenses d section  rental agreements  background  a cure worse than the disease  statuto